                <p><strong>Subscription Fees:</strong> You will incur subscription fees regardless of trading performance. Fees are non-refundable for completed billing periods.</p>
              </div>

              <h3 class="text-primary mb-3">6. REGULATORY AND TAX CONSIDERATIONS</h3>
              <div class="mb-4">
                <p><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> You are responsible for ensuring your trading activities comply with all applicable laws and regulations in your jurisdiction.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Tax Implications:</strong> Options trading may have complex tax implications. Consult with a tax professional regarding your specific situation.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Account Requirements:</strong> Options trading requires appropriate account approval from your broker and may have minimum account value requirements.</p>
              </div>

              <h3 class="text-primary mb-3">7. BEFORE YOU BEGIN TRADING</h3>
              <div class="mb-4">
                <p><strong>Education:</strong> Ensure you fully understand options trading, including the specific strategies you plan to use.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Risk Capital Only:</strong> Only use money you can afford to lose completely.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Start Small:</strong> Begin with small position sizes until you understand how the system performs.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Paper Trading:</strong> Consider paper trading or using sandbox mode before risking real capital.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Professional Advice:</strong> Consider consulting with a financial advisor who understands options trading.</p>
              </div>

